                  </rs>.</p>
               <p>SECOND COUNT, stating them to be the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t18200918-268-victim2502" type="victimName">
                     Thomas 
                     Pearson
                  <interp inst="t18200918-268-victim2502" type="surname" value="Pearson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-victim2502" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-victim2502" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-268-person2503">
                  ANN 
                  PEARSON
               <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2503" type="surname" value="PEARSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2503" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2503" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Underwood-street, Mile End. I sent 
               <persName id="t18200918-268-person2504">
                  Sarah 
                  Walton
               <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2504" type="surname" value="Walton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2504" type="given" value="Sarah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2504" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             with a bag to fetch these things from Courtney's, about two o'clock; she returned about three, with the bag empty.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-268-person2505">
                  SARAH 
                  WALTON
               <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2505" type="surname" value="WALTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2505" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2505" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am nine years old. Mrs. Courtney gave me this work in a bag, it was velveteen for breeches. As I came across the fields the prisoners followed me; Matthews knocked it out of my hand, and both ran away. I ran and screamed, and a man stopped Matthews, Richards got away, but was taken that night - I am sure of them both.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-268-person2506">
                  MARIA 
                  COURTNEY
               <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2506" type="surname" value="COURTNEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2506" type="given" value="MARIA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2506" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of Daniel Courtney, who is a tailor. I gave this child the materials for two pair of breeches, she put them in a canvas bag, and left about three o'clock - she went across the fields. I live in<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182009180099"></xptr>Storay-street. I found the prisoners in custody, with the property.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-268-person2507">
                  CHARLES 
                  EARL
               <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2507" type="surname" value="EARL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2507" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2507" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a smith. I was in the fields, and saw the prisoners about two hundred yards from the child. One said to the other,</p>
               <p>"Come, or we shall be too late." They went up to the child, Richards pushed her off the bank, and Matthews took the bundle. The child scrambled out of the ditch and ran after them screaming. I stopped Matthews with the property.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-268-person2508">
                  JOHN 
                  DOWNES
               <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2508" type="surname" value="DOWNES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2508" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-person2508" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I took Matthews in charge. She told me where to find Richards, and I took her in about an hour.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>MATTHEWS'S Defence. Richards had nothing to do with it.</p>

               <p>MATTHEWS - <rs id="t18200918-268-verdict1537" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200918-268-verdict1537" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 16.</p>
